# Alertmanager

Alert routing, grouping, silencing, and notification delivery.

- **Namespace**: `openshift-monitoring`
- **Pods**: `alertmanager-main-0`, `alertmanager-main-1` (StatefulSet, 2 replicas)
- **Upstream**: [prometheus/alertmanager](https://github.com/prometheus/alertmanager)
- **Downstream**: [openshift/prometheus-alertmanager](https://github.com/openshift/prometheus-alertmanager)
- **Jsonnet**: `jsonnet/components/alertmanager.libsonnet`
- **Config key**: `alertmanagerMain` in `cluster-monitoring-config`
- **Routing config**: `alertmanager-main` Secret in `openshift-monitoring`

## Key Investigation Metrics

- `up{job="alertmanager-main"}` — Target health
- `alertmanager_cluster_members` — Cluster size (should match replica count)
- `alertmanager_notifications_failed_total` — Failed notifications by integration
- `alertmanager_alerts` — Active alert count
- `ALERTS{alertstate="firing"}` — Currently firing alerts (via Prometheus)

## Common Issues

1. **Notifications not delivered**: Check `alertmanager_notifications_failed_total` by integration label, verify receiver config in `alertmanager-main` secret
2. **Cluster split-brain**: Check `alertmanager_cluster_members` — all replicas should agree
3. **Config inconsistency**: Check `alertmanager_config_hash` across replicas

For detailed queries see `components/alertmanager/queries.md`.
